quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,"I do not swear/make oath with that, the country/land"
  90,2,"And you are placed in/occupying (residing) at this , the country/land"
  90,3,And a father and what he gave birth (to)/procreated
  90,4,We had created the human/mankind in hardship
  90,5,Does he think/suppose that no one is capable/over powering on (over) him
  90,6,"He says: \"I destroyed/wasted plenty property/possession/wealth"
  90,7,Does he think/suppose that (E) no one sees him
  90,8,Did We not make/create for him two eyes
  90,9,"And a tongue , and two lips"
  90,10,And We guided him (to) the two paths/good or bad
  90,11,So he did not rush/force (himself) into the high mountain path/road
  90,12,And what made you know/informed you what the high mountain path/road (is)
  90,13,Releasing/freeing a neck/person/slave
  90,14,Or feeding in a day/time of hunger/starvation/famine
  90,15,An orphan of a relation/near/close
  90,16,Or a poorest of poor/poor oppressed of poverty
  90,17,"Then he was from those who believed and directed/commanded each other with the patience, and directed/commanded each other with the mercy/compassion"
  90,18,Those are the blessings`/right`s (side`s/hand`s) owners/friends/company
  90,19,"And those who disbelieved with Our verses/evidences , they are the bad omen`s/left side`s owners/friends/company"
  90,20,Stationary/residing fire (is) on them
  91,1,And/by the sun and its sunrise/day light
  91,2,And/by the moon when/if it followed it
  91,3,And/by the daytime when/if it shined/revealed it
  91,4,And/by the night when/if it covers/darkens it
  91,5,And/by the sky/space and who built/constructed it
  91,6,And/by the earth/Planet Earth and who spread and extended it
  91,7,And/by a self and who straightened it
  91,8,"So He inspired/transmitted (to) it its debauchery/corruption, and its fear and obedience of God"
  91,9,Who purified/corrected it had succeeded/won
  91,10,And who buried it/plotted against it (corrupted it) had failed/despaired
  91,11,Thamud had lied/denied/falsified with its own tyranny/excess of the limit
  91,12,When/if its most miserable/unhappy stirred up/urged
  91,13,"So God`s messenger said to them: \"God`s female camel, and its drink/drinking (water)"
  91,14,"So they denied him , so they wounded it/slaughtered it/made it infertile, so their Lord became angry/destroyed on them because of their crime, so He straightened it"
  91,15,And He does not fear its end/turn (result)
  92,1,And/by the night when/if it covers/darkens
  92,2,And/by the daytime when/if it uncovered/shined
  92,3,And/by what (who) created the male and the female
  92,4,That truly your striving/endeavor (is) separate/different (E)
  92,5,So but who gave/granted and feared and obeyed
  92,6,And gave charity/confirmed with the best/most beautiful
  92,7,So We will ease him to the ease/prosperity
  92,8,And but who was stingy/miser and sufficed/availed
  92,9,And lied/denied/falsified with the best/most beautiful
  92,10,So We will ease him to the difficulty/hardship
  92,11,And his property/possession/wealth does not enrich/suffice (replace) from him if he fell/was destroyed
  92,12,That truly on Us (is) the guidance (E)
  92,13,"And that truly for Us (is) the end (other life) (E), and the first/beginning"
  92,14,And so I warned you/gave you notice (of) a fire blazing/burning/inflaming
  92,15,None roasts/suffers it except the most miserable/unhappy
  92,16,Who lied/denied/falsified and turned away
  92,17,And the most fearing and obeying will be made to avoid it/be distanced from it
  92,18,Who gives/brings his property/possession/wealth (and) purifies/corrects (himself)
  92,19,And (there) is not to anyone at Him from a blessing/goodness to be rewarded/reimbursed
  92,20,Except wishing/desiring his Lord`s the highest`s/mightiest`s/most dignified`s face/front (path)
  92,21,And he/He will/shall (E) accept/approve
  93,1,And/by the sunrise/daybreak
  93,2,And/by the night when/if it quietened/became covered
  93,3,"Your Lord did not leave/desert you , and nor hate/hit (you) on the head"
  93,4,And the end (other life) (E) (is) better for you than the first/beginning
  93,5,"And your Lord will/shall (E) give/grant you , so you accept/approve"
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan , so he sheltered (you)"
  93,7,And He found you misguided so He guided (you)
  93,8,"And He found you having dependents/poor , so He enriched/satisfied (you)"
  93,9,"So as for the orphan , so do not humiliate/compel"
  93,10,"And as for the asker/questioner/beggar , so do not yell at/drive away"
  93,11,"And as for with your Lord`s blessing/goodness , so tell/inform"